The paper deals with autonomous mobile robots operating in a dynamic environment, which suggests that it could belong to the Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) category. The robots are exploring a graph, which could also place the paper in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) categories. The use of mobile robots and the exploration of a graph also suggest that the paper could belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) category. Finally, the paper analyzes the solvability of the problem in synchronous settings, which could place it in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category.
